tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2000
tnt3.description: A look back at the 1999/00 UEFA Champions League final between Real Madrid and Valencia in Paris. Steve McManaman, signed from Liverpool the previous summer, starred for Madrid.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2001
tnt3.description: We revisit the dramatic 2000/01 UEFA Champions League final between Bayern Munich and Valencia at the San Siro in Milan. Bayern were chasing their first title in a quarter-century.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2002
tnt3.description: The 2001/02 UEFA Champions League final saw a star-studded Real Madrid face Bayer Leverkusen in Glasgow. The match featured arguably the greatest goal in the competition's history.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2003
tnt3.description: We revisit the 2002/03 UEFA Champions League final between Juventus and AC Milan at Old Trafford. Paolo Maldini aimed to lift the trophy as captain, just as his father did in 1963.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2004
tnt3.description: We revisit the 2003/04 UEFA Champions League final between Monaco and Porto in Gelsenkirchen. Jose Mourinho would leave Porto to take over at Chelsea just days later.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2005
tnt3.description: The 2004/05 UEFA Champions League final saw Rafa Benitez's Liverpool take on AC Milan in Istanbul. The match would go down as arguably the greatest European Cup final in history.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2006
tnt3.description: The 2005/06 UEFA Champions League final in Paris saw Arsenal face a pre-Lionel Messi Barcelona, then under the command of Frank Rijkaard, and featuring Ronaldinho in his pomp.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2007
tnt3.description: We rewind back to the 2006/07 UEFA Champions League final at the Olympic Stadium in Athens as AC Milan looked to avenge their defeat two years previously against the Reds.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2008
tnt3.description: A look back at the 2007/08 UEFA Champions League final between Manchester United and Chelsea at Moscow's Luzhniki Stadium, the first all-English final in the competition's history.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2009
tnt3.description: A look back at the 2009 UEFA Champions League final between Barcelona and Man Utd in Rome. United were bidding to become the first team to defend the trophy in the modern era.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2010
tnt3.description: We revisit the 2010 UEFA Champions League final between Bayern Munich and Inter Milan at the Bernabeu. Jose Mourinho was looking to become the third man to win it with two clubs.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2011
tnt3.description: The 2010/11 UEFA Champions League final saw Manchester United come up against Pep Guardiola's Barcelona at Wembley, the scene of United's first European Cup success back in 1968.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2012
tnt3.description: We revisit the 2011/12 UEFA Champions League final between Bayern Munich and Chelsea at the Allianz Arena. This was Chelsea's second final, having lost their last in 2008.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2013
tnt3.description: We revisit the all-German 2013 UEFA Champions League final between Borussia Dortmund and Bayern Munich at Wembley. Bayern had lost two finals in three years.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2014
tnt3.description: The 2013/14 UEFA Champions League final in Lisbon saw Real Madrid go head-to-head with arch-rivals Atletico Madrid. Real aimed to become the first club to win the trophy 10 times.

tnt3.title: Champions League Final 2015
tnt3.description: We revisit the enthralling 2014/15 UEFA Champions League final between Juventus and Barcelona in Berlin. Barcelona were chasing their third Champions League title in six years.

tnt3.title: MotoGP Classics: Argentina 2018
tnt3.description: A look back at the classic 2018 MotoGP race in Argentina, where British rider Cal Crutchlow raced to victory and Marc Marquez and Valentino Rossi collided in the closing stages.

tnt3.title: MotoGP Classics: Assen 2018
tnt3.description: A look back at the classic 2018 Dutch Grand Prix. Marc Marquez came out on top in a race that produced the closest top 15 finish in the sport of all time.

tnt3.title: MotoGP Classics: Austria 2018
tnt3.description: Relive all the action from the classic 2018 MotoGP race in Austria. Jorge Lorenzo came out on top of a wheel-to-wheel battle fellow compatriot Marc Marquez.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Frozen II
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2019) The gang return for another magical adventure. Elsa must discover her destiny. And Anna, Kristoff and Olaf go along for the ride. Expect big laughs, bigger songs. But who's Samantha?

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: Homer and Apu: E4 resolves to bring you ten episodes where characters try something new. In this one, Homer joins Apu on a pilgrimage to the original Himalayan Kwik-E-Mart. (S5 Ep13/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: Hurricane Neddy: The Flanders' home is blown down by a hurricane and the Leftorium is looted. Homer leads the rebuilding project, but will Ned be happy with his new house? (S8 Ep8/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Old Man and the Lisa: Mr Burns loses all his money and employs Lisa to help him earn back his fortune. But they don't see eye to eye over ethical issues. (S8 Ep21/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: Pokey Mom: Marge notices a prison inmate's artistic talent and helps him to get a job painting a mural at the school. But he clashes with Skinner. Michael Keaton guest stars. (S12 Ep10/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: Worst Episode Ever: Bart and Milhouse end up running Comic Book Guy's shop after he has a heart attack. And, while he recovers, Comic Book Guy falls in love... (S12 Ep11/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: Hungry Hungry Homer: Homer goes on hunger strike when he discovers that the Springfield Isotopes baseball team are planning to move to Albuquerque. (S12 Ep15/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: Please Homer Don't Hammer 'Em: Marge discovers that she has a gift for carpentry, but has to use Homer as a cover in order to overcome prejudices against women builders. (S18 Ep3/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: G.I. (Annoyed Grunt): Homer accidentally signs up for basic training in the army. And Marge and Grampa get roped in when they try to get him released. (S18 Ep5/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: Ice Cream of Margie (With the Light Blue Hair): Marge, feeling overshadowed by Homer's new career selling ice cream, starts creating ice lolly stick sculptures. (S18 Ep7/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Get a Fresh Start
E4Plus1.uk.description: E My Sports: When Bart starts earning money from video game competitions, Homer becomes his coach, and their team make it to the finals in South Korea. (S30 Ep17/23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Movie
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2007) Animated comedy. When Homer's love for a pig causes world-threatening pollution, Springfield gets enclosed in a huge dome. D'oh! Will he do the decent thing and save his neighbours?

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners 2
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2014) Comedy sequel. The lads visit Jay in Australia after he tells them he's living a life of hedonism and sexual promiscuity as a superstar DJ.

Film4.uk.title: Deadpool 2
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Ryan Reynolds returns as the potty-mouthed, can of whup-ass-opening superhero and now he's got buddies to help him take on baddie Josh Brolin in the all-out action comedy sequel.

Film4.uk.title: Mission: Impossible - Fallout
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Tom Cruise stars in part six of the action-thriller series. His mission: to stop terrorists from getting their hands on nuclear bombs and unleashing global devastation.

Film4.uk.title: Funny Pages
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Dark, adults-only, coming-of-age comedy about a troubled schoolboy who quits education to become a comic book artist - with the help of an array of questionable older men...

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Anastasia
Film4.uk.description: (1997) Animated drama. When the Russian royal family is murdered, the sole surviving child is separated from her grandmother. Years later, conmen try to exploit the reward for her return.

Film4.uk.title: Monster House
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Spooky animated caper with Maggie Gyllenhaal and Steve Buscemi. A young boy and his babysitter spy on the creepy neighbour. Did he really eat his wife?

Film4.uk.title: Miracle on 34th Street
Film4.uk.description: (1994) Festive family drama. Richard Attenborough stars as a department store Santa who insists he's the real Santa Claus. But can he prove it in court?

Film4.uk.title: The Devil Wears Prada
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Comedy-drama starring Anne Hathaway and Meryl Streep. A naive young woman lands a job as assistant to one of New York's most important, but ruthless and cynical, magazine editors.

Film4.uk.title: Taxi
Film4.uk.description: (2004) All-action thriller. Queen Latifah stars as the driver of the fastest taxi in New York, who teams up with an inept cop (Jimmy Fallon) to catch a team of female bank-robbers.

Film4.uk.title: See How They Run
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Sam Rockwell and Saoirse Ronan head a splendid ensemble for this comedy whodunnit that places a real murder among a production of Agatha Christie's The Mousetrap. With Adrien Brody.

Film4.uk.title: Last Night in Soho
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Edgar Wright's horror with Thomasin McKenzie, Anya Taylor-Joy and Matt Smith. A fashion student's transported back to Swinging-60s London. But nostalgia's not what it used to be...

Film4.uk.title: The Entity
Film4.uk.description: (1982) Sidney J Furie's seminal horror stars Barbara Hershey as a divorced mother of three who becomes the victim of a poltergeist that submits her to multiple violent and sexual assaults.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Jingle All the Way
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Brian Levant's festive all-action comedy. Arnold Schwarzenegger is on a mission to get his son (Jake Lloyd) the must-have Christmas toy, Turbo Man. But it's sold out everywhere...

Film4.uk.title: Deck the Halls
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Comedy. Neighbours Matthew Broderick and Danny DeVito get extremely competitive as they festoon their houses with increasingly outrageous festive decorations and lights.

Film4.uk.title: The Black Swan
Film4.uk.description: (1942) Swashbuckling adventure with Laird Cregar and Tyrone Power. Privateer Captain Henry Morgan tries to rid the Caribbean of pirates when he's made Governor of Jamaica. Bit rich.

Film4.uk.title: Little Women
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Greta Gerwig's Oscar-winning period drama adaptation of the classic Louisa May Alcott novel, starring Emma Watson, Saoirse Ronan, Florence Pugh, Timothe Chalamet and Meryl Streep.

Film4.uk.title: Sleepless in Seattle
Film4.uk.description: (1993) Romantic comedy with Tom Hanks and Meg Ryan. A bereaved man gets another chance at love when his son puts him on a radio talk show.

Film4.uk.title: The Equalizer
Film4.uk.description: (2014) Thriller. Denzel Washington stars as an ex-soldier who comes out of retirement to help a teenage sex worker who's been assaulted by her pimp.

Film4.uk.title: Withnail and I
Film4.uk.description: (1987) Richard E Grant and Paul McGann star in Bruce Robinson's cult comedy as hard-drinking, substance-abusing unemployed actors who flee to Cumbria to escape their squalid London life.

Film4.uk.title: Walking and Talking
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Comedy with Catherine Keener and Anne Heche. A successful woman's best friend is getting married - making her feel unlucky in love. But is everything as rosy as it at first seems?

Film4.uk.title: The Lady Eve
Film4.uk.description: (1941) Screwball romcom with Barbara Stanwyck and Henry Fonda. A con artist is forced to change tack when she falls for her mark and he dumps her for trying to con him in the first place.

Film4.uk.title: The Straight Story
Film4.uk.description: (1999) David Lynch's fact-based drama with Richard Farnsworth. Alvin Straight drives hundreds of miles across the USA on a lawnmower to visit his dying brother - Harry Dean Stanton.

Film4.uk.title: The Golden Voyage of Sinbad
Film4.uk.description: (1973) Can Sinbad stop a master magician from reaching the Fountain of Destiny on the lost land of Lemuria and being crowned the new leader of Marabia?

Film4.uk.title: Stormbreaker
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Family action-thriller with Alex Pettyfer and Mickey Rourke. British intelligence recruit a schoolboy to take on the man who killed his dad and is planning to unleash a deadly virus.

Film4.uk.title: The Day the Earth Stood Still
Film4.uk.description: (2008) Remake of the sci-fi classic with Keanu Reeves. An alien visits Earth to tell humankind to stop destroying the planet. But when he's attacked, he decides to eradicate us instead...

Film4.uk.title: Mission: Impossible - Dead...
Film4.uk.description: ...Reckoning: (2023) Tom Cruise returns as Ethan Hunt and jumps a motorbike off a mountain for real. There's some stuff about an all-powerful AI. But it's the thrills that we're here for!
